com.google.api.ads.admanager.jaxws.factory

Class AdManagerServices

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.api.ads.common.lib.factory.BaseServices<AdManagerServiceClient,AdManagerSession,AdManagerServiceDescriptor>
      • com.google.api.ads.admanager.lib.factory.BaseAdManagerServices
        • com.google.api.ads.admanager.jaxws.factory.AdManagerServices
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AdManagerServicesInterface, AdsServicesInterface<AdManagerSession>

    public final class AdManagerServices
extends BaseAdManagerServices
    Utility class to create Ad Manager service clients. The session is stored as a reference within the client so that the session may be altered to affect the behavior of the client.

    Usage example: 

    
 AdManagerSession session = new AdManagerSession.Builder()...build();
 InventoryServiceInterface inventoryService =
    new  AdManagerServices().get(session, InventoryServiceInterface.class);
 campaignService.makeRequest(...);
 ...
 session.setNetworkCode(...);
 campaignService.makeRequest(...);

    Implementation is thread-safe.
